er (ch.468-479); from chapter “seventeen” to “sixty” the red ink number (479-522) is four less than the corresponding FM chapter number (ch.483-526); from chapter “sixty-one” to “ninety-one” (the last in the ms) there are no red ink numbers – and these correspond to FM ch.527-557. In summary, the text of RG 35 K. al-Aqṭāb has the appearance of a highly abbreviated version of FM ch.462-557, omitting ch.480-482 entirely. It is possible that RG 35 is an early form or summary of sifr 17 of the first recension text of FM.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>4/74-195 as Aqṭāb al-Muḥammadiyya wa manāzilihim.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>&lt;638?</DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="19" RECORDID="425"><COL><DATA>41.1</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>425</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>R. [fī] al-Arwāḥ</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>رسالة في الأرواح</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Probable IA.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>arwah</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>IA</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Treatise on the angelic spirits and their different categories (lost in love/muhayyama, organising the heavens/musakhkhira, and organising bodies/mudabbira). Similar in content to Fut.III.201, where the same categories of spirits are discussed (ch. 348).</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Only one ms, Zahiriye 5433/241b-242b. It is styled as a separate treatise, but may be either K. al-Arwāḥ (mentioned in Fihrist) or drawn from passages in the Futuhat.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>133</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>143</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>9. 267, 268, 351</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="54" RECORDID="429"><COL><DATA>47</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>380</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>429</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Asrār ḥurūf al-muʿjam</DATA></COL><COL><DATA> أسرار الحروف المعجم</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Verified A</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>asr_hur</DATA></COL><COL><DATA> </DATA></CO