abashī and Ibn Sawdakīn in Aleppo in 611H because it had incited the disapproval of some of the local ʿulamāʾ.  </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>A much copied work, verified by two historic mss., Evkaf Muzesi 1713 (873H) and Fatih 5322 (934H), which are both copied from originals written by Ayyūb b. Badr, with samāʿ dated 626H and 616H resp. Most mss. also include the full text of the Tarjuman (RG 767), of which there are also some separate copies.Copy in Baghdad, Iraq Museum 11086/2 which a cataloguer believed was copied in the 7th century (al-Furqān online: https://www.al-furqan.com/our_is_item/manid/1250158/groupid/139348) See: مخطوطات الأدب في المتحف العراقي = Makhṭūṭāt al-adab fī al-Matḥaf al-ʿIrāqī = Catalogue of Manuscripts of Literature In the Iraq Museum Library, p.444 (#1155). After transcribing the usual text in which IA gives the reason he wrote the work the catalogue has this:فرغ منه المؤلف سنة 614H بمدرسة الامير مظفر الدين محمودThis information does not occur in most mss: completed 614H in the madrasah of Amīr Muẓaffar al-dīn Maḥmūd.  (It occurs in the Shuqayrī edition of 1995). </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>184</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>III, 129.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>640</DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="66" RECORDID="285"><COL><DATA>102</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>101</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>285</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>al-Dīwān al-kabīr</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>الديوان الكبير</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Verified A.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>diwan</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>IA</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>634H</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Damascus</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>lammā badā al-sirr fī fuʾādī</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Ibn ʿArabi’s collected poems, containing more than 800 verses, compiled in the last years of his life and finished in 634H. There are are several different versions of the work, including a six volume holograph of which we do not, at the moment, have a complete copy. Research is therefore ongoing to produce a de