d-alone mss. are Manisa 6596 (undated, taken from SQ’s copy), and Ragib Pasha 1453 (although very late, probably also taken from SQ’s copy). There is an issue with the preface on this work. There are two basic variants; some mss carry the same preface as the commentary, Dhakhāʾir al-alāq (RG 116. Others have a longer version which begin with a khutba and IA’s account of meeting the young girl, Niẓam, who inspired the poems in Mecca. The situation is complex, with several other variants appearing in some mss (see Jane Clark Mystical Perception and Beauty: Ibn ʿArabī’s Preface to Tarjumān al-Ashwāq in JMIAS 55, 2013). </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>176</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>&lt;800</DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="66" RECORDID="261"><COL><DATA>802</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>261</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>ʿUqlat al-mustawfiz</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>عقلة المستوفز</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Verified A.</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>uql_mus</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>IA</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>al-ḥamdu lillāh alladhī iftataḥa wujūd al-siwā bi-l-arwāh al-muhayyamiyya al-makhlūqa </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>The perfect human being (al-insān al-kāmil) and the multiple degrees of Being from the most elevated orders of the Archangels to inorganic nature (OY).  </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>An often copied work, verified by three historic mss. The best is Yusuf Ağa 4690  (undated and incomplete, but  in IA’s handwriting); also Shehit Ali 1341 (725H, said to have been taken from an original, which may have been by IA) and Ayasofya 4875 (dated 753H). </DATA></COL><COL><DATA>19</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>19</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>&lt;638</DATA></COL></ROW><ROW MODID="55" RECORDID="394"><COL><DATA>821</DATA></COL><COL><DATA></DATA></COL><COL><DATA>394</DATA></COL><COL><DATA>Waṣiyya fī kayfiyyat ḥuṣūl al-maʿrifa al-q